The test dataset has a few categorical features containing values that are not present in the training dataset, which may result in inaccurate prediction if these are import features in the trained model. Although there are only 24 records, will try to find a solution in the analysis later.¶

plt.ylabel('Total explained variance')

plt.xlim(0, 364)

plt.axvline(80, c='b')

plt.show()

3 Model Training¶

3.1 Train the model using XGBoost by utilizing the data with reduced dimensions¶
In [28]:
import xgboost as xgb
from sklearn.metrics import r2_score
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

x_train, x_valid, y_train, y_valid = train_test_split(arr_x_train_pca, df_y_train, test_size = 0.2, random_state = 4242)

dm_train = xgb.DMatrix(x_train, label = y_train)
dm_valid = xgb.DMatrix(x_valid, label = y_valid)

xgb_params = {
    'objective': 'reg:squarederror',
    'eta': 0.02,
    'max_depth': 4,
    #'subsample': 0.7,
    #'colsample_bytree': 0.7,
    #'silent': 1
}

def xgb_r2_score(preds, dtrain):
    labels = dtrain.get_label()
    return 'r2', r2_score(labels, preds)

watchlist = [(dm_train, 'train'), (dm_valid, 'valid')]

model_pca = xgb.train(xgb_params, dm_train, 1000, watchlist, early_stopping_rounds=50, feval=xgb_r2_score, maximize=True, verbose_eval=10)

Features such as X5 are seen critical. As pointed out in section 1.7, X5 in test data has value not present in training dataset.¶
3.3 Create another model by removing these features to predict for records pointed out in section 1.7¶
In [33]:
list_features_to_remove = ['X0', 'X2', 'X5']
df_x_train_reduced = df_x_train.drop(columns = list_features_to_remove)

x_train, x_valid, y_train, y_valid = train_test_split(df_x_train_reduced, df_y_train, test_size = 0.2, random_state = 4242)

dm_train = xgb.DMatrix(x_train, label = y_train)
dm_valid = xgb.DMatrix(x_valid, label = y_valid)

xgb_params = {
    'objective': 'reg:squarederror',
    'eta': 0.02,
    'max_depth': 4,
    #'subsample': 0.7,
    #'colsample_bytree': 0.7,
    #'silent': 1
}

def xgb_r2_score(preds, dtrain):
    labels = dtrain.get_label()
    return 'r2', r2_score(labels, preds)

watchlist = [(dm_train, 'train'), (dm_valid, 'valid')]

model_reduced = xgb.train(xgb_params, dm_train, 1000, watchlist, early_stopping_rounds=50, feval=xgb_r2_score, maximize=True, verbose_eval=10)
